io.craigmiller160.stockmarket.gui.dialog

Class SellDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.craigmiller160.mvp.listener.AbstractListenerDialog
      • io.craigmiller160.stockmarket.gui.dialog.AbstractDefaultDialog
        • io.craigmiller160.stockmarket.gui.dialog.TransactionDialog
          • io.craigmiller160.stockmarket.gui.dialog.SellDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.craigmiller160.mvp.listener.ListenerDialog, io.craigmiller160.mvp.listener.ListenerView, java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.util.EventListener

    @NotThreadSafe
public class SellDialog
extends TransactionDialog
    A dialog for performing a sell shares transaction. The maximum limit on the quantity of shares is the number of shares owned of the stock. The amount of shares selected by this dialog will be "sold", and the profits will be added to the cash balance available to buy more stocks.

    THREAD SAFETY: Swing is NOT thread safe.

    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    craig

    • Method Detail

      • setStock

        public void setStock(Stock stock)
        Set the stock that is being used in this transaction. NOTE: the stock needs to already have downloaded its values, or else this operation will take place with outdated data, or possibly not even have the necessary data at all.

        This class will only accept an OwnedStock as a parameter, because only a stock that is owned and has a quantity value can have shares be sold. If the parameter is not an OwnedStock, an exception is thrown.

        Overrides:
        setStock in class TransactionDialog
        Parameters:
        stock - the stock that is being used in this transaction.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the stock parameter is not an instance of OwnedStock.
